On Jul 15, 2006, at 5:44 PM, Wayne wrote:

> I've got a '79 bus and just threw the alt fan belt.  As I'm putting  
> on the
> new belt, I'm trying to move the alt to tighten up the belt and  
> can't figure
> where to get some leverage.  I looked in Bentley and it just says  
> to set
> tension so there is 5/8" movement.  I'm having trouble moving the  
> alt to get
> it that tight.  What am I missing?

To loosen the belt you can squeeze it together with two hands.

To tighten, stick a screw driver in the gap above the t-slot nut and  
bolt and lever down on it.  It doesn't have to more far...

